# Optional cloud auth + sync (Supabase). Copy to .env.local and fill in with
# your project's values from Supabase dashboard -> Settings -> API.
# Leave unset to run AUDAX fully local-first (no account needed).
#
# NEVER put real values in this file (.env.example is committed to git).
# NEVER put the service-role / secret key in a VITE_ variable or anywhere in
# this app — it bypasses Row Level Security and must never reach the client.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Optional AI Health Coach (OpenRouter), used only by the Health page.
# CRITICAL: these must NEVER be prefixed with VITE_ — a VITE_ variable gets
# bundled into the client JS and would let anyone extract your key from the
# deployed site's DevTools. These are read ONLY by api/health-coach.js, a
# Vercel serverless function that runs server-side and proxies the request —
# the browser never sees this key. Set them in Vercel's dashboard (Project ->
# Settings -> Environment Variables), not in a VITE_-prefixed local .env, for
# them to take effect in production.
# Get a free key at https://openrouter.ai/keys, then pick any model tagged
# ":free" from https://openrouter.ai/models to set OPENROUTER_MODEL.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
OPENROUTER_MODEL=meta-llama/llama-3.2-3b-instruct:free
